# Delete workspace

Deleting a live session that is attached to a named jj workspace should kill the
tmux session, forget the workspace, and remove the workspace directory.

    :bins jj tmux cat test sh

> [!NOTE]
> 'jj', 'tmux', 'cat', 'test', and 'sh' are available.

    :copy tests/fixtures/jjconfig.toml .jjconfig.toml (copied)

    :t rename-session -t 0 runner (success)
    :$ jj git init alpha (exit: 0)
    :$ jj describe -R alpha -m "alpha commit" (exit: 0)

First create a workspace-backed session through `sesh`, so the session has the
same metadata as normal user-created workspace sessions.

    :t new-session -d -s create "sesh -r alpha; cat" (success)
    :t resize-window -t create:0 -x 120 -y 12 (success)
    :pane create:0.0
    :settle -d 2s (settled)
    :k alpha C-r C-u feature Enter
    :settle -d 2s (settled)

Launch a fresh picker and select the workspace-backed session.

    :t new-session -d -s ui "sesh; cat" (success)
    :t resize-window -t ui:0 -x 120 -y 12 (success)
    :pane ui:0.0
    :settle -d 2s (settled)

    :k feature
    :snap "/\d{4}-\d{2}-\d{2} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{1,2}/t" "/(?:@|○|◆)\s+([a-z]{8})/w" "/\b([0-9a-f]{8})\b/h"

```terminal
session: feature
  1/4 | [C-r] repo: ~/alpha.feature, [C-o] onto: trunk() | [C-d] delete, [C-x] close
   alpha/feature~1                          ~/alpha.feature~1                                                          ┃
▌⬤ alpha/feature                            ~/alpha.feature                                                            ┃
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
@  wwwwwwww (no email set) ttttttttttttttttttt feature@ hhhhhhhh
│  (empty) (no description set)
│ ○  wwwwwwww (no email set) ttttttttttttttttttt default@ hhhhhhhh
├─╯  (empty) alpha commit
◆  wwwwwwww root() hhhhhhhh


```

Requesting deletion should mark the selected session and show the confirm
shortcut.

    :k C-d
    :settle (settled)
    :snap --color "/\d{4}-\d{2}-\d{2} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{1,2}/t" "/(?:@|○|◆)\s+([a-z]{8})/w" "/\b([0-9a-f]{8})\b/h"

```terminal
session: feature
  1/4 | [C-r] repo: ~/alpha.feature, [C-o] onto: trunk() | [C-y] confirm, [C-x] close
   alpha/feature~1                          ~/alpha.feature~1                                                          ┃
▌× alpha/feature                            ~/alpha.feature                                                            ┃
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
@  wwwwwwww (no email set) ttttttttttttttttttt feature@ hhhhhhhh
│  (empty) (no description set)
│ ○  wwwwwwww (no email set) ttttttttttttttttttt default@ hhhhhhhh
├─╯  (empty) alpha commit
◆  wwwwwwww root() hhhhhhhh


```

![light](delete-workspace.md.snap.2.light.svg)
![dark](delete-workspace.md.snap.2.dark.svg)

Confirming should remove the tmux session, remove the workspace from jj's
workspace list, and delete the workspace directory.

    :t set-hook -g session-closed "set-hook -gu session-closed; wait-for -S deleted-workspace-session" (success)
    :k C-y
    :t wait-for deleted-workspace-session (success)
    :settle -d 2s (settled)

    :t has-session -t alpha/feature (failure)

```
can't find session: alpha/feature
```

    :$ jj workspace list -R alpha --ignore-working-copy --no-pager --color never --template 'name ++ "\n"' (exit: 0)

```stdout
default
```

    :$ sh -c 'test ! -e alpha.feature' (exit: 0)

